         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Botanic Gardens 26/3/67 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ One of the boys employed in this establishment (William Lamley jun.) having recently died, I have now the honor to solicit, that you will be pleased to grant me auth...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">67.03.26b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James McCulloch</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Q67/3108, unit 254, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS written<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ernst Heyne and signed by M.</p>
               </note>Botanic Gardens 26/3/67</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>One of the boys employed in this establishment (William Lamley jun.) having recently died, I have now the honor to solicit, that you will be pleased to grant me authority to pay the wages due to him for work performed (from the first of March to the 20th 17<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>days at 3/.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>per day) to his father Will. Lamley sen., also employed in this establishment, who is the rightful owner, the boy having been under age.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The honorable the Chief Secretary<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation: 'Approved J McC 1/4/1867'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The request form, addressed to the Governor<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in Council, is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>included in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>file. The sum of £2.11.0 was approved. The paperwork was forwarded<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>by the Undersecretary, J. Moore, to M on 13 April<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>annotated: 'the Director of the Botanic Gardens is requested to append a certified copy of the Order in Council to the pay sheet and return the papers'. M returned the papers<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>on 17 April marked: 'Request complied with &amp; best thanks tendered'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[Q67/3869, unit 254, VPRS 3991,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Public Record Office, Victoria].</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
